         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">17/6/85 ¶  ¶ It was with much gratification, dear Mr Pulsford, that I received this evening the photogram, which the gallant Capt. Everill left for me as a souvenir, and which I value all the more, as...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.06.17</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Pulsford</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.2134/1, Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (NSW Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17/6/85</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It was with much gratification, dear Mr Pulsford, that I received this evening the photogram, which the gallant Capt. Everill left for me as a souvenir, and which I value all the more, as I never met him personally.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No image<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Everill<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been identified at MEL, but see M to J. Haast, 29 July 1862 (in this edition as 62-07-29b) and notes thereto.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have no photographic card of my own at hand as a return-gift to the Leader of the Expedition;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>New Guinea exploring expedition.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but if I knew, whether any sending of mine would reach him still, I would forward it to such place, as you might suggest, perhaps Thursday-Island. I should like to thank him also for his farewell-telegram,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Telegram not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which reached me late on Saturday night, I being absent from home til then, thus too late to send a return-telegram</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This evening I also received the copy of instructions, with the tenor and fullness of which I am much pleased.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pulsford (1885).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I have not been always so attentive in writing to you, as could be wished, I must remark in extenuation of my shortcomings, that I am most onerously engaged in my Department, in as much as this year enormous extra-work has to be done for the Colonial Exhibition in London,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Colonial and Indian Exhibition, London, 1886.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and as I have two large new works under the press,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B85.02.05, B85.12.03.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— the correspondence from my own hands being anyhow already about 3000 letters a year!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We here also are very grateful to you for the zeal, displayed by you, in getting your own large share done for the fitting out of the expedition in the responsible position, which you so honorably occupy.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
